date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2019
review_content: Medium is a great sized bag! It’s great for the gym, where I can put a basketball, pair of shoes, toiletry bag, and a change of clothes easily in this bag. author: Jonathan
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2019
review_content: I wasn’t sure if I should get the large or extra large. Ended up getting the large and there is plenty of space. I do MMA training and this bag fits everything. Gloves, shin pad, hand wraps, jump rope, jiu jitsu gi, and still enough room for a change of clothes. title: Plenty of pockets and space.
verified: Color: Graphite Medium Heather (040)/SilverSize: LargeVerified Purchase

author: Lifted Performance
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2021
review_content: Look this bag is perfect for what I was looking for. A small gym bag to carry a change of clothes and all my trinkets…. wrist wraps etc and even a 36” tricep rope. I hate people that don’t specify what they got, so I ordered the XSMALL. I wanted the smallest bag to carry around but still have plenty of room. And this nailed it. Super good amount of space for the size, and plenty sturdy. I carry it with me my entire workout station to station so I needed something compact. I’m also not a moron and did some research beyond the one picture on this listing. People said the bag they ordered didn’t have clips for the strap or a very front zipper on the front pocket. Well that’s because u ordered a S OR XS. It’s not hard to do a tad bit of research folks. If u go to the under armour site I’ll see that the S and XS have slightly different features. It has a front pocket but no small zipper on the outside of that pocket. And the straps r connected on both, the removable straps r only on M and up. I specifically got the XS cause I don’t care lol. I’m just using it as a gym bag so having the attached strap is perfect. Plenty of room even in the XS, front pocket is just an open compartment (no cell phone divider or anything like that). The shoe compartment is great , I use that for my towel and dirty clothes and more smelly items as it has a vent for air. Great all around bag , just do research before u pick the size for Christ’s sake!!!
title: XS bag is the perfect gym bag. Point blank

review_content: This is a good gym bag, very functional.  Have no negatives.  My problem is the Amazon ad.  It comes in S,M,L, and XL. The large is still a little large for my use.  My use is that I go to the gym early in the morning, work out, then shower, shave and dress for work.  So I have about the maximum amount of stuff for typical use.  (I’m a big guy with big feet-requiring size 13 shoes).  The large size is still too large.  I wish I had gotten the medium- my fault.  My only complaint is the outside mesh carrier is too small for a water bottle and a small travel bag I keep ear buds, heart monitor, access card.

author: sdwolfe
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2020
review_content: I hope this review helps someone else who is looking into buying this duffel bag ( I didn’t see too many reviews of the large black one ) this bag looks pretty big on me and I’m 5’3”- 180 pounds. In one picture I used a queen size pillow to show the width of the bag. You can probably fit two of those pillows and still have some room.This bag is definitely bigger than I expected but I’m happy I went with the large size instead of medium because having extra space is better than not having enough space. I got this for my husband to use for short trips or when he has to work an overnight shift. It fits a large, adult sized throw blanket, a small pillow , a couple pairs of clothes, a pair of size 10 men’s shoes, and a toiletry bag and still leaves a lot of room left. You could probably fit a week or two weeks worth of clothes in it.There’s a shoe pocket on one side which I think is so cool so you can separate shoes from all the other things you want to put in it. It has a small pocket inside of it, big enough to fit a wallet or phone, etc. , a front zipper pocket that you can fit small items In, plus another pocket on the opposite side of the shoe pocket that you can fit a couple of full sized shampoo bottles In (just to give you an idea of size) . It comes with an adjustable, removable strap to wear on your shoulder and the material of the bag is pretty thick and durable.Overall I’m so happy I purchased this and my husband said it is perfect and exactly what he needs. We use underarmour products all the time and they don’t disappoint.
title: Durable and spacious

date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2020

author: Daniel
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 12, 2020
review_content: I do like this bag. The red color is pretty sharp. The “small” bag is very generous and I am able to fit my size 11 sneakers in the compartment, a pair of 12oz boxing gloves, wraps, a change of clothes, a small tub of preworkout, two water bottles in the mesh side compartment, my wireless headphones, and other knick knacks and snacks. I am pleased with it.The reason for the negative review is that I can not recommend a product that did not come compete. In the uploaded photo the wide comfort piece to the shoulder strap did not come with the bag (see product photos). I will not be returning as I read it is a common occurrence when I was looking at reviews, and ultimately for the price this bag suits my needs as is.If you won’t be disappointed not to get that little piece for the shoulder strap, then it is a great bag worthy of an initial impression rating of 5 stars. Time will tell its durability and water resistance and I hope to update the review accordingly.

author: Robert Smith
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2020
review_content: I got this bag for a gym bag. I love the look and feel of this duffel. Black and gray looks very sharp. Zippers feel quality. Smooth and no snags. The D ring clip on the front is a nice touch. As is the soft lined small pocket on the inside for items you don't want scratched. I ordered the small and it has plenty of room for everything I need. My only gripe is maybe have an even smaller version available as this actually has a lot of unused space for how I use it. I just go from my house to the gym and I am dressed for a workout already when I go. If you take a bag to the office and need all your workout gear and clothes in the bag this may suit you. The side open shoe compartment is great for this purpose. Overall I definitely recommend this bag if you are looking for a go-to gym bag.

author: Jonathan Hensley
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2021
review_content: I ordered the Medium Under Armour Adult Undeniable Duffle 4.0 Gym Bag.  This is what I received, and in the correct color I selected too.  I managed to cut one of the straps taking off some of the wrapping, but this is my fault.However.The description says this bag is machine wash and this was one of the requirements I had when looking for a duffle bag.  The care instructions tag inside the bag tells me that this should not be machine washed.  The exact text is below:Do not wash (the bag can be spot cleaned with a damp cloth and allowed to dry naturally)Do not bleachDo not tumble dryDo not ironOther than this (blatant) false advertising in my opinion (by whomever wrote the description), it appears to be an excellent duffle bag.  I'm still rather annoyed.
title: Inaccurate description on Amazon: Not machine washable according to the care tag inside the bag
verified: Color: Black (005)/Metallic Gold LusterSize: MediumVerified Purchase

author: Jenn
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2020
review_content: The title isnt a joke. I, a 22 year old average sized female, could fit inside of this bag. It was difficult, but I could fit. If you think you need a medium, you likely do not.I go to the gym 3 times a week before class. I need EVERYTHING to get ready. 2 towels, full outfit, makeup bag, shampoo, conditioner, lotion, hair product, blow dryer, flat iron, curling iron, extra shoes, you name it. Plus extra workout gear like bands, water bottle, foam roller, etc.After looking at the reviews, I decided to go with a medium. Based on the pictures I thought that would be a reasonable size.I was wrong. This is massive. I can literally fit myself into the medium size bag. An entire body in one bag (hopefully there are no crazy axe murderers reading this review). Guys, I'm not kidding, I put my entire bathroom and 2 extra outfits in this bag and I still have so much room.So the space is great. But carrying it? Not great. The bag is freaking giant, I can't stress this enough. Its not uncomfortable to carry but just be aware this is much larger than you think. If you're like me and just wanna fit your ridiculous 10 step beauty routine, you probably just need a small. If you're someone who packs his own home gym into his gym bag to bring to the gym? Go with a medium.Tldr - great bag but so much larger than you'd think. Seriously, order a size down.
title: The medium can fit an adult human inside

author: Seabass
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2020
review_content: This bag is a pretty good gym bag. Its quite deep, i can pack my gym clothes and my son's swim shorts,  2 towels in the main compartment with extra room to spare. The very front pocket is shallow, good for money or keys. The 2nd front pocket is large. I put my project rock headphones(in the case), lifiting gloves, multiple hygiene products and brush. The inside pocket in the main compartment can hold my Samsung galaxy 8 and keys but there is no zipperThe vented shoe pocket can fit my size 13 shoes. The shoulder strap works really well and stays in place. That was why i tried this bag instead of returning to my Adidas bag.The 1 thing i think that could be improved is the other end pocket is a mesh pocket and could be better with zipper to hold more stuff. And maybe a zipper for the inside pocket. But overall i am very happy with this bag
title: Very functionality gym back worth the money if you work out or need a small travel bag

author: Robert
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2020
review_content: I originally purchased the bag strictly for gym use. However, I quickly started to use the bag for short weekend trips. The bag can accommodate about three days worth of clothes and other essential weekend items.The separate shoe compartment is handy and can easily fit my size 11 shoe. Inside the main compartment, there is a small pouch to store jewelry or a cell phone in. There is an elastic exterior pouch on the end of the bag, which is great for items you need to grab n the go, such as a water bottle or cell phone. Lastly, there is a small exterior zipper pouch. The pouch is not very big but can handle a deodorant, wallet, and toothbrush with a little room to spare.The bag does not have any framework and although it stands up on its own now, I think in time with usual wear and tear, it will not hold its shape as well.Being a tall person (6'5''), it is always hard finding a bag that doesn't look like I am using a child's back or so large I look like I am packing for a holiday in Europe. The bag doesn't look out of proportion and wears will on a tall person.This is a very nice bag, and I would purchase another.
title: Great Gym Bag of Weekender

A sturdy bottom would help when loading/unloading the bagCinch on exterior drawstring pocket. Would help water bottles stay secure.Contrasting interior color. author: zackattack

They would also come in handy for toothbrushes,  shoes,  shampoo/ conditioner,  money,  makeup,  nail polish, notebooks,  passports... anything little you wanted to keep separate and safe.  My daughter will be going on a trip this summer,  so I'm about to order one just like this for her. I might even have to order one for myself. I'm very happy with these... they are VERY roomy too, good thick quality.  Not cheap or flimsy.

Apparently we were sold a used bag.

author: Lifted Performance
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2021
review_content: Look this bag is perfect for what I was looking for. A small gym bag to carry a change of clothes and all my trinkets…. wrist wraps etc and even a 36” tricep rope. I hate people that don’t specify what they got, so I ordered the XSMALL. I wanted the smallest bag to carry around but still have plenty of room. And this nailed it. Super good amount of space for the size, and plenty sturdy. I carry it with me my entire workout station to station so I needed something compact. I’m also not a moron and did some research beyond the one picture on this listing. People said the bag they ordered didn’t have clips for the strap or a very front zipper on the front pocket. Well that’s because u ordered a S OR XS. It’s not hard to do a tad bit of research folks. If u go to the under armour site I’ll see that the S and XS have slightly different features. It has a front pocket but no small zipper on the outside of that pocket. And the straps r connected on both, the removable straps r only on M and up. I specifically got the XS cause I don’t care lol. I’m just using it as a gym bag so having the attached strap is perfect. Plenty of room even in the XS, front pocket is just an open compartment (no cell phone divider or anything like that). The shoe compartment is great , I use that for my towel and dirty clothes and more smelly items as it has a vent for air. Great all around bag , just do research before u pick the size for Christ’s sake!!!

date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2021
review_content: This duffle is advertised as having a "removable padded shoulder-strap" when in fact it has a permanently fixed unpadded strap. Not sure where the removable straps are, seeing as I searched all UA bags and didn't see this feature even in previous versions. I am not sure yet if I will return it, but did think it was a decent enough discrepancy to share because it does take away from the value of this bag as well as how comfortable it is to carry around with decent weight in it. Also, I think it's worth mentioning that I wear size 8 women's shoes and I had to cram them to fit in the shoe storage pocket. I realize the bag is XS, but still it was a tight fit so really don't think any larger shoes or men's shoes would fit very well. One thing I did really like right away was a little loop at the base of one end of the bag, so I can hang it vertically in a gym locker as my gym only has square or tall rectangular lockers.
